Cloud masking of Sentinel-2 images with Google Earth Engine (GEE) can be done using the built-in "Sentinel2CloudScore" algorithm. This algorithm is based on the "sen2cor" algorithm developed by the European Space Agency (ESA) and it uses a combination of spectral bands to identify and mask clouds, clouds shadows, and cirrus clouds.
Here's an example of how to apply the cloud masking algorithm to a Sentinel-2 image in GEE:
```php
// import the Sentinel-2 image
var image = ee.Image('COPERNICUS/ST000000_20210101T235959_T32UPU');
// apply the cloud masking algorithm
var cloudMask = image.select('QA60').bitwiseAnd(1 << 10).eq(0);
// apply the cloud mask to the image
var cloudFreeImage = image.updateMask(cloudMask);
// display the cloud-free image
Map.addLayer(cloudFreeImage, {bands: ['B4', 'B3', 'B2'], min: 0, max: 3000});
```
